# --- Param-URL duplicates ------------------------------------------------------
# NOT handled here. Cloudflare _redirects cannot match on query strings: a rule
# written as `/?keywordutm_source=google  /  301` parses as plain `/`, which makes
# the homepage 301 to itself — an infinite loop that takes the whole site down.
# (That shipped once and was caught on the preview deploy.)
#
# The malformed `?keyword`/`?utm_source` dupes the old site leaked into the index
# are handled instead by:
#   - robots.txt  ->  Disallow: /*?
#   - a self-referencing <link rel="canonical"> on every page, which folds any
#     ?param variant back into the clean URL.
# If a param URL ever needs a true 301, do it with a Cloudflare Redirect Rule
# (those can match query strings); never in this file.
